                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>When an alchemical golem takes physical damage from a critical hit or is affected by a shatter spell, one glass chamber within its body shatters, spewing alchemical liquid in a 5-foot emanation. Roll on the alchemical chambers list (see above) to determine which one shatters-on a roll of 1-5, creatures in the area take [[/r 10d6 #damage]]{10d6 damage} of the appropriate type (<span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"28\" data-pf2-traits=\"damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Alchemical Rupture DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span>). On a roll of 6, creatures must instead save against the sickness effect.</p>"
